description:
&lt;p&gt;How would you like to come and work in a dynamic and forward thinking endoscopy unit based at St George’s University Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust?  We have 6 rooms and undertake a wide range of procedures including Upper and Lower GI, ERCP, EBUS, alongside being and accredited with JAG and has the Bowel Cancer Screening Centre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We pride ourselves on putting our patients first and provide a supportive environment for staff for training in Endoscopy both in the formal and informal setting.  You will be based at SGH but you  can have the opportunity to work at Queen Mary’s Hospital, Roehampton and The Nelson based in Wimbledon.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; We are looking for band 5 nurses, ideally with 6 months post registration experience to come and join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Vicki Hedley - vicki.hedley@stgeorges.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;David Calayag - david.calayag@stgeorges.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
